sub_topic: Prove that the empty set is a subset of every set.
message_1: Let A be a set containing 5 elements. Determine whether the empty set ∅ is a subset of set A or not.
message_2: Yes, the empty set ∅ is a subset of set A. By definition, the empty set is a subset of every set, including set A, regardless of the number of elements in set A.
